    "This shifts learning toward tokens with higher task utility, improving convergence on reasoning benchmarks.",
    "Algorithmfor batch in dataloader: outputs = model(**batch) loss = weighted_loss(outputs.logits, batch.labels, batch.rewards) optimizer.zero_grad() loss.backward() rank_allocator.update(loss, model) apply_new_ranks(model) optimizer.step() Listing 1: DRaFT-Q fine-tuning loop 3.6 Computational Complexity DRaFT-Q adds minimal overhead to standard LoRA.",
